arch:property.oc:show_val: Large midden with plenty of diagnostic and scrap material. Mostly sheep/goat, but some cattle, equid (teeth and one metapodia), pig teeth and calcaneum, turtle, microfauna (recovered from dry sieve), carnivore (mustelid and canid), and bird (represented by bone and eggshell). Human bone and a coprolite were also recovered. The scrap is largely sheep-goat size, but small to cow-size animals are also represented. Age range includes perinatal to adult in all size categories There is an even distribution of body parts for sheep-goat and cattle, but low on vertebrae and rib heads. Vertebrae, metapodia, astragali, and phalanges, in particular, show signs of digestion. Gnawing is evident throughout the assemblage, including the scrap. Several pieces of sheep/goat mandible have polish on coronoid process and some rounded edges possibly from trampling or water wear. Burning appears sparse and sporadic. Moderate weathering (3-4) appears most consistently, but this varies. Not many indications of coherence. Generally appears to be the typical large midden of mostly sheep-goat derived from multiple activities, but not a street, where we would expect much more trampling. While much of the assemblage appears heavily processed big pieces of fragile elements have survived. Located below 8859, and is comparable in size but less fragmented. Like 8859 (but not like TP middens), it has much digestion but not much burning or cut marks. Several pieces of worked bone recovered. No DNA samples taken. Last F number = 3456. (WOW!)
Rhian Mayon-White, Ian Cameron, Katheryn Twiss,Kamilla Pawlowska, Adam Watson
